Write the isClosed method in the Loop class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class Loop {
    isClosed() {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class Loop {
    isClosed() {
        if (this.edges.length < 2) {
            return false;
        }
        const firstVertex = this.edges[0].getStartVertex();
        const lastVertex = this.edges[this.edges.length - 1].getEndVertex();
        return firstVertex === lastVertex;
    }
}
```
